President Trump met with President Buhari of Nigeria to discuss issues related to terrorism and trade. They discussed a trade deal for military equipment and expressed their commitment to combating terrorism. President Trump also mentioned the serious problems faced by Christians in Nigeria and promised to address the issue. President Buhari expressed gratitude for the support of the United States in fighting terrorism and highlighted the historical context of the jihadist problem in Nigeria. They also discussed the efforts to rescue the Chibok and Dapchi girls who were kidnapped by Boko Haram. The meeting concluded with President Trump mentioning ongoing discussions on immigration.